cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CR 

This paper deals with automatic post-disaster damage detection using aerial imagery, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of imbalanced classification, which is a common issue in machine learning, and hence, it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning for damage detection, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics) as well. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of detecting damage caused by disasters, which could also be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
